column5: I thought I'd share my version of a surf & turf diner I had tonight    since I couldn't go fishing today    mother nature had PMS again   dumping a load of snow yesterday   and today... blowing her north westerly @25km/h  Ain't no way this sorry ass was going out   So to begin this 2 course meal, first, had to thaw my rainbow filets and deer steak in cold water    Then prepped the tatters and veggies    Got the pans hot    Dropped the rainbow filets in the pan and the tatters      First course Ummm!    Then got the venison prepped with olive oil, soya sauce, worcestershire (spell check here lol) salt & pepper    Dropped the veggies and venison in the pan      Second course Ummm!    Ate like a king    Even had left over for breakfast tomorrow    Tomorrow my daughter is competing for YBC National... if they finish first... their going out east to Newfoundland  Tight lines Leechman
Fantastic.  Venison has got to be my favourite game meat, and rainbow definitely among my favourite fish.
WOW!!! Awesome looking an sure taste excellent!
Boy does that look delish....  Makes me want to lick the screen
makes me want to live at his house
I like the ratio of Meat 'n Fish to taters and Veggies......this man knows how to roll!
Awesome Jacques!!  Good luck to your daughter
looks great Jacques  couple ??  Is that zuchinni in the vegs and did you fry those spuds in oil or butter?

Thanks guys!!! much appreciated!!! Frankie.... just got back from todays tournament and the girls finished second with silver medals   now got to go clean viruses on the main computer  Typing from the WII console  Terrence, yes zuccini, celery, carrots and mushroom...  everything was cooked in butter
That looks awesome Jacques. I would love to eat dinner at your place.
It was Chris!!!  Anytime your up this way... drop in for some good eats
No more WII stuff... Got the computer back on track... friggin trojans   Thank god I had a Ghost image to restore
Thanks Sinclair!!!  No, not at all     The smell, at the time was awesome
